HEADWORD: Laurestine
<hw>Lau"res*tine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>lautus
tinus</ets>, fr. L. <ets>laurus</ets> the laurel + <ets>tinus</ets>
laurestine. See <er>Laurel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
<spn>Viburnum Tinus</spn>, an evergreen shrub or tree of the south of
Europe, which flowers during the winter months.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>laurustine</asp> and <asp>laurestina</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

